<figcaption class="blocks-gallery-caption">Applying Bone Meal to my self seeded organic papaya tree</figcaption></figure>



<p>The bone meal requires soil microbes to decompose it makes the phosphorous and calcium plant available. So you need to apply it by digging a trench around the rooting zone. Apply 2-3 tablespoons for a large tree in the ground. After adding bonemeal cover the trench with soil and water it thoroughly to start the decomposition process.</p>



